      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Córdova the 19th of November 1884 ¶ Baron Ferdinand von Mueller ¶ Melbourne ¶ Respected Sir ¶  ¶ In two different consignments I am sending you per post No 4  ¶ Quercus xalapensis ¶  and No 5  ¶ Querc...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">84.11.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Hugo Finck</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M142, Library, Royal Botanical Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with specimens of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Quercus</seg> sp. (MEL 2419305-6),</p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marked by M: ‘Beantw. 25/1/85 F.v.M. Mexico via San Francisco’ [Answered 15 January 1885]. Letter not found.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Córdova the 19th of November 1884</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Herrn Baron Ferdinand von Müller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Geehrter Herr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In zwei verschiedenen Remessen sende ich Ihnen per Post No 4 <name key="Quercus%20xalapensis">Quercus xalapensis</name> &amp; No 5 Quercus sp ?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Quercus%20xalapensis">Quercus xalapensis</name> has a wide range, it is found on the eastern declivities of the Orizába mountains from the height of 2 to 5.000 feet above the level of the sea. It is generally found in red cly, where nothing else will grow and seems to spring spontaneously on any clayey exhausted soil. Attains the height of 60 to 80 feet, is a quick grower, giving heavy crops of acorns. Its timber will only stand under roof, is of a whitish colour and here mostly used for fuel.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 5. Quercus sp ? (red oak) is a lofty oak 60 to 80 ft high, furnishing excellent timber for building purposes. Pigs are very fond of its acorns. No 4 &amp; 5 have deciduous leaves.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tannen und Fichtensamen sind mir noch nicht gebracht worden, hoffe aber bald davon zu erhalten.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herzlichst grüssend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ergebenst der Ihrige</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hugo Finck</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Meine Sendung vom 14tn Novber mit Eicheln No 3 werden Sie erhalten haben.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Córdova the 19th of November 1884</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Ferdinand von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respected Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In two different consignments I am sending you per post No 4 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Quercus%20xalapensis">Quercus xalapensis</name>
               </seg> and No 5 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Quercus</seg> sp ?.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Quercus%20xalapensis">Quercus xalapensis</name>
               </seg> has a wide range, it is found on the eastern declivities of the Orizába mountains from the height of 2 to 5,000 feet above the level of the sea. It is generally found in red clay, where nothing else will grow and seems to spring spontaneously on any clayey exhausted soil. Attains the height of 60 to 80 feet, is a quick grower, giving heavy crops of acorns. Its timber will only stand under roof, is of a whitish colour and here mostly used for fuel.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M cited Finck as a source of data on <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Quercus%20xalapensis">Quercus xalapensis</name>
                     </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Q. xaloepensis</seg>) in B84.13.22, p. 319, and in subsequent editions, but retained reference to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Q. xalapensis</seg> without details in this and subsequent editions under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Q. sideroxyla</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No 5. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Quercus</seg> sp ? (red oak) is a lofty oak 60 to 80 ft high, furnishing excellent timber for building purposes. Pigs are very fond of its acorns. No 4 &amp; 5 have deciduous leaves.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Fir and pines seeds have not yet been brought to me but I hope to get them soon.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sincere greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Most humbly your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hugo Finck</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">You will have received my consignment of 14 November with acorns No 3.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Quercus%20xalapensis">Quercus xalapensis</name>
            </p>
         </div>
